<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40045e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40045e">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40045e"> 45(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> devil &mdash; present / <font face="wake">+</font> = future</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Gnostics held that &ldquo;the present world sprang from a fall of man, or from an undertaking hostile to God, and is, therefore, the product of an evil or intermediate being&rdquo; (p. 257). Some taught that while the future had been assigned by God to Christ, the devil had received the present age (p. 309). <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 122</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
